6 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 35e, is
7 amended to read as follows:
8 Section 35e. A. It shall be the duty of the superintendent,
9 principal or head teacher of each public or private middle, junior
10 high and high school accredited by the State Department of Education
11 in the State of Oklahoma to notify the Department annually as
12 scheduled by the Department of the name, address, race and age of
13 any pupil dropping out from the school during the preceding year.
14 The report shall be made on forms prescribed and furnished by the
15 Department.
16 B. The State Board of Education shall cause these statistics of
17 school dropouts to be tabulated by grade and school district.
18 Information of school dropouts shall be made available to the
19 Oklahoma Department of Career and Technology Education, the Bureau
20 of Indian Affairs, the Military Department of the State of Oklahoma
21 for use in the youth educational programs provided by the Department
22 and the State Department of Health.
23 C. The State Department of Education shall make an annual
24 report to the Legislature prior to the convening of each regular
