3 D. For the purposes of this section, "school dropout" means any
4 student who is under the age of nineteen (19) and has not graduated
5 from high school and is not attending any public or private school
6 or is not otherwise receiving an education pursuant to law for the
7 full term the schools of the school district in which the student
8 resides are in session. School dropouts shall not include students
9 whose departures have been reported in accordance with Section 1 of
10 this act.
11 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
12 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
13 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
14 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
15 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
